The paper deals with graph coloring and recoloring, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of tree decompositions is a common technique in algorithm design for graphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also discusses the treewidth of graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.GT).
